<html><p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Micro Focus Hybrid Cloud Management X (HCMX) simplifies the delivery, consumption, and governance of IT services and resources. HCMX is delivered as part of a single converged solution that provides the capabilities of HCMX and Service Management Automation X (SMAX) integrated Configuration Management System (CMS) and Operations Orchestration (OO) solution. HCMX offers the following cloud management capabilities:</span></span></span></p>

<ul>
	<li style="margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Design and Deploy (DND)</span></span></span></li>
	<li style="margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Cost governance and resource optimization (CGRO)</span></span></span></li>
	<li style="margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Image aggregation</span></span></span></li>
	<li style="margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">IT process orchestration</span></span></span></li>
	<li style="margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Service portal</span></span></span></li>
	<li style="margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Content store</span></span></span></li>
	<li style="margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Universal CMDB</span></span></span></li>
	<li style="margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">CMS UI</span></span></span></li>
	<li style="margin-bottom:11px; margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Mobile application</span></span></span></li>
</ul>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">The HCMX image aggregation functionality aggregates images from multiple cloud providers and displays those images in a single web page.&nbsp;An administrator selects one of the aggregated images and exposes it to end users as a service offering. Aggregated images include images from Amazon Web Services (AWS) Marketplace, Microsoft Azure Marketplace, Private images from AWS and Azure and VMware vCenter templates. For example, Wordpress image is an image from AWS Marketplace and it can be selected from a list of aggregated images and exposed to end users as a service offering. &nbsp;End users can then order, provision and cancel those service offerings. The HCMX image aggregation functionality provides the following benefits:</span></span></span></p>

<ol>
	<li style="margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Control over list of images available to end users.</span></span></span></li>
	<li style="margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Image visibility can be different depending on business needs of their business unit.</span></span></span></li>
	<li style="margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Control over the region to which end users can provision those images.</span></span></span></li>
	<li style="margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Control over the image instance size that end users can provision.</span></span></span></li>
	<li style="margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Ability to pre-select least cost images from among multiple cloud providers and expose to the end users.</span></span></span></li>
	<li style="margin-bottom:11px; margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Ability to use approval process before an image is provisioned in the target cloud provider.</span></span></span></li>
</ol>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">This practitioner note describes steps involved in configuring HCMX image aggregation functionality, using image aggregation to expose one of the aggregated images to end users and using one of the exposed images to provision and manage those services.</span></span></span></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:11px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">This practitioner note has the following sections:</span></span></span></p>

<ol>
	<li style="margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Configure image aggregation</span></span></span></li>
	<li style="margin-bottom:11px; margin-left:8px"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">Use image aggregation</span></span></span></li>
</ol>

